FBIS3-54955 "drsov003_b_94042" FBIS-SOV-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Local Commanders Discuss Internal Troops' Problems PM0401124394 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1500 GMT 23 Dec 93 PM0401124394 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By Sergey Shevtsov and Aleksandr Vissarionov; from the "Novosti" newscast] [Excerpt] [Shevtsov over video of troops on maneuvers] For the internal troops, just as for the entire country, this year has been extremely difficult and even dramatic. In the most difficult conditions, officers and men continued to guard important state installations and special cargoes as well as corrective-labor camps. Together with other internal affairs personnel they performed successfully in the special operations Gastroler, Signal, Koltso and Arsenal. In the state of emergency regions troop units carried out over 70 operations, seized thousands of firearms and other weapons, and saved the lives of hundreds of innocent people. This and many other difficult problems and tasks for the internal troops were discussed today by Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs okrug commanders and troop training establishment chiefs who participated in an all-Russia rally.
